-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----
< Replace this block with the TLS server-cert trust anchor(s) for your SCEP
  endpoint.  Most NDES deployments terminate HTTPS with a cert issued by the
  same enterprise/root CA that signs SCEP-issued device certs, so this is
  usually 1-2 PEM-encoded certs: the root, and optionally the issuing CA.

  To dump the chain from a live server:

      openssl s_client -showcerts -connect scep.example.com:443 -servername scep.example.com </dev/null \
        | awk '/-----BEGIN/,/-----END/'

  And to fetch the root from the AIA URL of the leaf or intermediate:

      curl -fsSL "$(openssl x509 -in chain.pem -text -noout | grep -A1 'CA Issuers' | tail -1 | awk -F': ' '{print $2}')" \
        | openssl x509 -inform DER

  This file is gitignored. >
-----END CERTIFICATE-----
